:[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Adding metadata and tests**\\n\\nI’m considering whether I need to add metadata for Class.forName. Class.forName should usually support classes if they’re reachable, right? In a native image, this works for registered classes. I think if a constant is known and reachable, it might be folded, but there could be challenges with legacy synthetic strings. I want to create a dedicated test file mapping for the RolloverFileOutputStream and use @TempDir to ensure proper file construction and assertions.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Validating date handling and file operations**\\n\\nI’m looking at how to use new Date and format with UTC. Should I use LocalDate instead, or is DateTimeFormatter acceptable? I’m considering potential issues with time boundaries, especially if something crosses midnight. Instead of focusing on exact date strings, maybe it’s better to assert that the filename doesn’t contain the formatted date. I think I need to capture the dated filename right after writing, then flush and close the stream before reading the content. Also, I should determine if my `append` setting makes sense.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering constructor issues**\\n\\nI’m thinking about whether an issue might arise if the first constructor fails due to the RolloverFileOutputStream.class already being loaded. I realize that the static field class$ only gets initialized when the class’s code executes. Just loading the class itself doesn't trigger that initialization. So, it seems like it should be fine, but I need to keep an eye on this to avoid potential problems later on.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_73wghYNO8TNr8yQUfk9slJGg|fc_02a42abd782526d80169f4fc322b88819791698899531b3b68", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.mortbay.jetty/jetty-util/6.1.26/src/test/java/org_mortbay_jetty/jetty_util/RolloverFileOutputStreamTest.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage org_mortbay_jetty.jetty_util;\n\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.io.TempDir;\nimport org.mortbay.util.RolloverFileOutputStream;\n\nimport java.nio.charset.StandardCharsets;\nimport java.nio.file.Files;\nimport java.nio.file.Path;\nimport java.util.TimeZone;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\npublic class RolloverFileOutputStreamTest {\n    @TempDir\n    Path temporaryDirectory;\n\n    @Test\n    void createsDatedLogFileAndWritesBytes() throws Exception {\n        Path rolloverPattern = temporaryDirectory.resolve(\"rollover-yyyy_mm_dd.log\");\n        String datedFilename;\n\n        try (RolloverFileOutputStream stream = new RolloverFileOutputStream(\n                rolloverPattern.toString(), false, 7, TimeZone.getTimeZone(\"UTC\"))) {\n            stream.write(\"jetty rollover\".getBytes(StandardCharsets.UTF_8));\n            datedFilename = stream.getDatedFilename();\n\n            assertThat(stream.getRetainDays()).isEqualTo(7);\n            assertThat(stream.getFilename()).endsWith(\"rollover-yyyy_mm_dd.log\");\n            assertThat(datedFilename).doesNotContain(\"yyyy_mm_dd\");\n        }\n\n        Path datedFile = Path.of(datedFilename);\n        assertThat(datedFile.getParent()).isEqualTo(temporaryDirectory);\n        assertThat(Files.readString(datedFile, StandardCharsets.UTF_8)).isEqualTo(\"jetty rollover\");\n    }\n}\n"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 457, "output": 987, "cacheRead": 25088, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 26532, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777663014169, "responseId": "resp_02a42abd782526d80169f4fc2699f88197a8921f3988b28d0e"}}
[tool-exec] start id=call_73wghYNO8TNr8yQUfk9slJGg|fc_02a42abd782526d80169f4fc322b88819791698899531b3b68 name=write args={"path": "tests/src/org.mortbay.jetty/jetty-util/6.1.26/src/test/java/org_mortbay_jetty/jetty_util/RolloverFileOutputStreamTest.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage org_mortbay_jetty.jetty_util;\n\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.io.TempDir;\nimport org.mortbay.util.RolloverFileOutputStream;\n\nimport java.nio.charset.StandardCharsets;\nimport java.nio.file.Files;\nimport java.nio.file.Path;\nimport java.util.TimeZone;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\npublic class RolloverFileOutputStreamTest {\n    @TempDir\n    Path temporaryDirectory;\n\n    @Test\n    void createsDatedLogFileAndWritesBytes() throws Exception {\n        Path rolloverPattern = temporaryDirectory.resolve(\"rollover-yyyy_mm_dd.log\");\n        String datedFilename;\n\n        try (RolloverFileOutputStream stream = new RolloverFileOutputStream(\n                rolloverPattern.toString(), false, 7, TimeZone.getTimeZone(\"UTC\"))) {\n            stream.write(\"jetty rollover\".getBytes(StandardCharsets.UTF_8));\n            datedFilename = stream.getDatedFilename();\n\n            assertThat(stream.getRetainDays()).isEqualTo(7);\n            assertThat(stream.getFilename()).endsWith(\"rollover-yyyy_mm_dd.log\");\n            assertThat(datedFilename).doesNotContain(\"yyyy_mm_dd\");\n        }\n\n        Path datedFile = Path.of(datedFilename);\n        assertThat(datedFile.getParent()).isEqualTo(temporaryDirectory);\n        assertThat(Files.readString(datedFile, StandardCharsets.UTF_8)).isEqualTo(\"jetty rollover\");\n    }\n}\n"}
